---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from "../../lib/seo";

const lastUpdated = "2026-07-07";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the Malice Mizer Research Archive — cookieless Vercel Web Analytics, no advertising, no identifiable user tracking."
  noindex
>
  <section class="card privacy-intro">
    <h2>Privacy policy</h2>
    <p class="muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <p>
      {SITE_NAME} ({SITE_URL}) is a static research archive. We do not run advertising,
      sell data, or build user profiles. This page explains what happens when you visit the site.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not set cookies.</li>
      <li>We use Vercel Web Analytics for aggregate page-view counts — not advertising or cross-site tracking.</li>
      <li>We do not collect names, email addresses, or other information you submit through this site.</li>
      <li>We do not use browser storage (localStorage or sessionStorage) to remember you.</li>
      <li>Fonts, styles, and images on most pages are served from this site — not from third-party CDNs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>What we do not collect</h2>
    <p>
      The site has no accounts, newsletters, contact forms, or comment systems. Browsing pages here
      does not create a profile tied to you on our side. We see only aggregate traffic metrics
      (such as which pages are visited and from which countries), not individual visitor identities.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Web analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We use{" "}
      <a href="https://vercel.com/docs/analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Vercel Web Analytics
      </a>{" "}
      to understand aggregate traffic — for example which archive pages are most visited and which
      countries visitors come from. It is cookieless, does not use advertising identifiers, and does
      not build cross-site profiles. We do not use Google Analytics or other ad-tech trackers.
    </p>
    <p>
      Analytics requests are served from this site on Vercel (or from Vercel’s analytics script host
      during local development). See{" "}
      <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Vercel’s privacy policy
      </a>{" "}
      for how they process data as our host.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Hosting and server logs</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on Vercel. Like most web hosts, Vercel may automatically process standard
      connection data in server logs — for example your IP address, browser type, requested page,
      and timestamp — to deliver the site, prevent abuse, and maintain reliability. Standard server
      logs are separate from the Web Analytics dashboard described above.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Fonts and static assets</h2>
    <p>
      Heading typefaces (Cormorant Garamond) are bundled with the site and served from the same
      domain as the pages themselves. We do not load fonts from Google Fonts or any other external
      font service. Body text uses fonts already available on your device.
    </p>
    <p>
      Images and other static files are also hosted on this site. Loading a typical archive page
      does not trigger requests to advertising networks or font CDNs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Third-party resources</h2>
    <p>
      Aside from hosting (above), the only third-party content loaded within the site is:
    </p>
    <dl class="privacy-list">
      <div>
        <dt>Web analytics</dt>
        <dd>
          Vercel Web Analytics (see above) loads on every page to record aggregate page views.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>Embedded videos</dt>
        <dd>
          Some concert pages include embedded players from YouTube, Internet Archive, Niconico, or
          Vimeo. Those players load only on the pages where they appear. The embedded service may
          set its own cookies or collect usage data under its own policy.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt>External links</dt>
        <dd>
          Pages link out to source archives, GitHub, and other sites. Once you leave this archive,
          the destination site’s privacy practices apply.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Corrections via GitHub</h2>
    <p>
      The footer links to GitHub to suggest corrections. If you open an issue there, you are
      interacting with GitHub under{" "}
      <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        GitHub’s privacy statement
      </a>
      , not submitting data to this archive directly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      This archive is intended for general research use and does not knowingly collect personal
      information from anyone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Content and licensing</h2>
    <p>
      Bibliographic data and English translations on this site are offered under{" "}
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="license noopener">
        CC BY-NC 4.0
      </a>
      . Site code is open source under MIT. Mirrored scans and magazine pages remain third-party
      property. See the <a href="/legal">legal &amp; licenses</a> page for the full policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If our practices change, we will update this page and the date above. Material changes — for
      example adding analytics or cookies — would be reflected here before or when they take effect.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be raised through{" "}
      <a href="https://github.com/susssus/mizermaxxer/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        GitHub issues
      </a>
      .
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .privacy-intro h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .privacy-list {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .privacy-list dt {
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .privacy-list dd {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  section.card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  section.card li + li {
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
  }
</style>
